description:
&lt;p&gt;A rare opportunity has arisen within the Community Continence &amp; Urology Service, Cheshire &amp; Wirral NHS Partnership Trust ( Physical Health ) for a Band 6 Continence &amp; Urology Nurse Specialist. This is a permanent post of 37.5 hrs per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic individual who has an interest in the specialities of continence and urology. You will form part of a well established integrated team who provide specialist care across CWP community neighbourhoods, clinics and care homes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful autonomous practitioner will require excellent communication skills and be a critical thinker, demonstrating high levels of decision making and problem solving.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To provide expert knowledge to professionals, service users and carers in regard to continence issues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lindsey McDonough&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Acting Community Continence &amp; Urology Service Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;lindsey.mcdonough@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;0151 488 8230&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact the service to arrange a visit to meet the team.&lt;/p&gt;
